./CHANGELOG.md:5:- Added depth-2 generation request end-to-end test coverage (frac-0079): `tests/test_generation_request.py` now includes `TestGenerationRequestEndToEnd`, which drives the `GenerationRequest` data structure through the full lifecycle of request creation, rejection of invalid types and boundaries, hash stability independent of backend/model string choices, hash divergence on generation parameter changes, and immutability. `tests/test_generation_request_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2. Existing per-function assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/request.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:7:- Added depth-2 generation health end-to-end test coverage (frac-0078): `tests/test_generation_health.py` now includes `GenerationHealthEndToEndTests`, which drives the IDyOM KL-divergence audit through real temporary LTM files, rolling history persistence, collapse alert output, JSON-safe `AuditReport.to_dict()` round-trips, no-auto-rollback hash preservation, and the config-driven `_main()` path via `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG`. `tests/test_test_generation_health_depth.py` pins the health test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation-health assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/health.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4517 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:9:- Added depth-2 generation composer-hook end-to-end test coverage (frac-0077): `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` now includes `GenerationComposerHookEndToEndTests`, which drives the public composer-hook surface (`_should_queue_now`, `build_generation_request`, `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD`) plus the duet-composer integration `_post_song_generation_hook` through the full gate -> build -> enqueue cycle. The end-to-end scenarios cover a happy-path enqueue with a real builder via a thin `_ConditionerAdapter` that asserts the queued payload equals `build_generation_request(...)`, idempotency key matches `request_hash`, and the request hash is a 64-char content-addressed digest; gate-denial paths for low daily budget at the `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD` floor, sampler-dominating antipatterns, working-ambience low arc payoff, and rate-limited recent enqueue under `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, all confirming `_post_song_generation_hook` returns `None` with no queue traffic; deterministic-builder identity for equal inputs and distinct hashes/seeds for changed mode or arc phase; and a JSON-safe round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` on the built request and the queued payload. `tests/test_test_generation_composer_hook_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function composer-hook assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4514 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:11:- Added depth-2 generation client protocol end-to-end test coverage (frac-0076): `tests/test_generation_client_protocol.py` now includes `GenerationClientProtocolEndToEndTests`, which drives a typed `GenerationRequest` through a structural `GenerationClient`, typed `GenerationResult` output, JSON-safe `result_summary`, `cost_per_second`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` success/failure diagnostics. `tests/test_test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins the protocol test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` behavior remains unchanged because the protocol helpers already produced meaningful output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4508 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:13:- Added depth-2 generation cache end-to-end test coverage (frac-0075): `tests/test_generation_cache.py` now includes `GenerationCacheEndToEndTests`, which drives the public `GenerationCache` API through the full miss → put → hit → replace cycle (asserting content-addressed filenames, suffix preservation, accessed-at LRU updates, and in-place byte replacement), the queue/storage `set`/`get` aliases sharing a single on-disk entry with `put`/`lookup`, a JSON-safe index round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, a multi-entry restart that recovers surviving entries while pruning a payload deleted out-of-band, and a combined count + size LRU cap where an explicit lookup keeps the oldest entry warm and forces eviction of the middle entry. `tests/test_test_generation_cache_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_cache.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation cache assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/cache.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4504 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:15:- Added depth-2 garden watcher end-to-end test coverage (frac-0074): `tests/test_garden_watcher.py` now includes `GardenWatcherEndToEndTests`, which drives the public garden watcher path through deterministic brightness/time snapshot building, JSON-safe operator summary generation, and atomic runtime-state persistence. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/garden_watcher.py` now exposes `build_garden_state`, `summarize_garden_state`, and `write_current_garden_state`, while `update_garden_state` delegates through the deterministic builder so existing callers keep the same one-path behavior. `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` pins the garden watcher test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4498 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:17:- Added depth-2 gallery-x11-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0073): `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` now includes coverage for `load_playlist`, `render_art`, `render_overlay`, and `init_pygame_display` using mocked data and a dummy SDL driver. A scoping bug in `my-claw/tools/gallery/gallery_x11.py` where overlay rendering logic was inadvertently placed inside `init_pygame_display` was fixed. A depth gate ensures `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` is pinned at fractal depth >= 2. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:19:- Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:21:- Added depth-2 federation-discovery end-to-end test coverage (frac-0071): `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` now ships a `FederationDiscoveryEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `discover_peers`, `save_peer_registry`, `load_peer_registry`, and `merge_peer_registry` surface end-to-end through fakes for `tailscale status --json` and the `/federation/v1/identity` endpoint. The end-to-end scenarios cover the full discover → save → load → re-scan → merge → save cycle (verifying meaningful `PeerInfo` fields, JSON-safe registry payloads, `to_dict`/`from_dict` round-trips, online/offline flag flips for vanished peers, `first_seen` preservation for returning peers, and online-on-arrival semantics for new peers), multi-IP peer fall-through where a later IP responds after an earlier IP refuses, and an empty rescan that marks every previously seen peer offline while preserving its identity and timestamps. `tests/test_test_federation_discovery_depth.py` pins `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class, loading `sdp.fractal.classify_depth` via `importlib.util` to remain deterministic against the local classifier. Existing function-level federation discovery assertions and the production `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4483 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:23:- Added depth-2 dashboard-generator coverage and the simplest Observatory-backed class path (frac-0070): `tests/test_dashboard_generator.py` now includes `DashboardGeneratorEndToEndTests`, which builds temporary SDP, Observatory, and pet-state inputs and verifies `generate_dashboard(...)` renders meaningful service, pipeline, pet class/level, event, and timestamp output without scripts. `tests/test_test_dashboard_generator_depth.py` pins the dashboard-generator test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. `my-claw/tools/dashboard_generator.py` now derives pet class overrides from Observatory `agent_skills` by mapping known skill categories to existing dashboard classes, accumulating score-weighted sample counts, selecting one dominant class per agent, and passing those overrides through `generate_dashboard(obs_db=...)`; missing or unreadable Observatory databases still return no class overrides. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4479 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:25:- Added depth-2 counterpoint_rules end-to-end test coverage (frac-0069): `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` now ships a `CounterpointRulesEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public counterpoint registry surface (`best_rule_for_phase`, `rules_for_phase`, `rules_for_leader_role`, `rules_for_follower_role`, `rules_for_voice_pair`, `resolve_rule`, `get_rule`, `motion_profile`, `analyze_dissonance`, `verify_resolution_sequence`, `resolution_completeness_score`, `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, `counterpoint_pair_summary`) end-to-end through 11 scenario tests covering: per-phase best-rule resolution against the documented Divination/Emergence/Conversation/Convergence/Crystallization expectations with affinity bounded in [0, 1]; voice-pair query intersections and unknown-role empty-result handling; `resolve_rule` known/alias/unknown fallback chains plus registry fallback validity; mixed-sequence motion classification including single-note and mismatched-length safe defaults; contrary-motion `score_counterpoint_fit` / `rank_counterpoint_rules` agreement with `recommend_counterpoint_rule` and bounded sub-metrics; realistic melody/bass dissonance + resolution analysis with JSON-safe annotation payloads; `counterpoint_pair_summary` payload shape, key set, JSON round-trip, and consistency with the underlying `CounterpointFit`; registry coverage equality with `REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIPS` and `REQUIRED_PHASES`; mixed-dissonance resolution completeness and weighted-smoothness penalties; voice-pair-compatible-only ranking for melody/bass pairs; phase-sensitive summary differences with JSON round-trip; and parallel/static/oblique extreme motion-profile sequences. `tests/test_test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestRegistryCompleteness`, `TestEntryFields`, `TestArcPhaseAffinity`, `TestVoicePairQueries`, `TestLookups`, `TestIntervalConstraints`, `TestImmutability`, `TestVerificationAndScoring`, and `TestDissonanceMetadata` assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4476 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:27:- Added depth-2 contact-mic calibration runtime test coverage (frac-0068): `tests/test_contact_mic_calibration_runtime.py` now includes `ContactMicCalibrationEndToEndTests`, a hardware-free class that drives the existing public calibration harness through JSON-safe WAV analysis, multi-channel activity metrics, fake-backend calibration bundle persistence, per-scenario JSON reports, `summary.json`, CLI `list-scenarios` / `analyze` JSON output, and ALSA device parsing/fallback behavior. `tests/test_test_contact_mic_calibration_runtime_depth.py` pins the runtime test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing contact-mic assertions and `my-claw/tools/contact_mic_calibration.py` production behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4463 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:29:- Added depth-2 constitution end-to-end test coverage (frac-0067): `tests/test_constitution.py` now ships a `ConstitutionEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `Constitution` API end-to-end through 30 scenario tests covering JSON rule loading and field mapping, missing/None path fallback, malformed-JSON tolerance, unknown-extension JSON fallback, regex matching, keyword matching with case-insensitive substring comparison, combined pattern + keyword rules where either path matches, phase and agent filtering (active and inactive), compound phase + agent gating, phase-agnostic rule fan-out across every phase argument, message-vs-description fallback, `hard_rules` / `soft_rules` / `rules_for_phase` filtering, and the full evaluate → `should_block` pipeline under each `EnforcementMode` (MONITOR, SOFT, FULL) including empty-violation no-block in every mode and multi-rule violations carrying the right `rule_id`, severity, and message. `tests/test_test_constitution_depth.py` pins `tests/test_constitution.py` at fractal depth >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`) and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestConstitutionLoading`, `TestConstitutionEvaluate`, `TestConstitutionHelpers`, and `TestShouldBlock` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/constitution.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4458 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:31:- Added depth-2 config end-to-end test coverage (frac-0066): `tests/test_config.py` now includes `ConfigEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing public config surface through init-project scaffold loading, save/load round trips, validation issue reporting, enabled-agent ordering, status reports, JSON-safe summaries, `load_or_default`, command-agent persistence, and `cmd_show_config` JSON payload shape. `tests/test_test_config_depth.py` pins `tests/test_config.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `ConfigTests` assertions and production `promptclaw/config.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4427 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:33:- Added depth-2 coherence-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0065): `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` now ships a new `TestCoherenceEngineEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public `CoherenceEngine` and `NullCoherenceEngine` surface through complete end-to-end paths. The new tests walk every hook in canonical order (`pre_routing → post_routing → pre_lead → post_lead → pre_verify → post_verify → finalize`) and verify event types, phases, monotonic sequence numbers, run-id propagation, and SQLite persistence across an engine rebuild; write a `constitution.json` with one HARD and one SOFT keyword rule and confirm `EnforcementMode.FULL` blocks `post_routing`/`post_lead`/`post_verify` while `EnforcementMode.MONITOR` records the same violations without blocking, propagating HARD severity, both rule ids, and a negative trust delta on `post_lead`; record two architectural decisions through `record_decision` and confirm `pre_routing`/`pre_lead`/`pre_verify` inject the `## Active Decisions` block with at least one matching title; step the graduation manager across three `finalize` calls plus alternating `record_graduation_observation` outcomes and verify the run/observation/true-/false-positive counters and stable enforcement mode; round-trip a full replayed event payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys and verify each event's `sequence_number`, `run_id`, and dict `payload`; and loop `NullCoherenceEngine` across multiple run ids confirming every hook returns an approved verdict with empty violations and empty injected context plus an empty replay. `tests/test_test_coherence_engine_depth.py` pins `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestCoherenceEngine` and `TestNullCoherenceEngine` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/engine.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4421 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:35:- Added depth-2 local-client end-to-end test coverage (frac-0064): `tests/test_client_local.py` now includes `TestLocalAdaClientEndToEnd`, which drives the existing `LocalAdaClient` public surface through typed `GenerationRequest` and legacy mapping paths. The new tests verify typed requests produce real mono WAV previews with stable local request ids, protocol summaries, zero-cost metadata, expected latency from an injected clock, valid WAV container metadata, nonzero frames, and passing `validate_generation_result` outcomes; verify mapping requests return queue/cache/storage-ready payloads with `prediction_id`, `api_request_id`, `request_id`, `audio_path`, `sample_rate`, duration, model, cost, per-second cost, and nonnegative latency; round-trip request summaries and combined diagnostics through `json.dumps`; and confirm repeated mapping generation reuses the same deterministic path and bytes. `tests/test_test_client_local_depth.py` pins `tests/test_client_local.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing local-client assertions and production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4414 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:37:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
