s` for configuration and the dependency injection pattern in `create_app` for testability. The logging configuration aligns with the structured logging conventions used in other parts of the project.\n\n## Security\nThe API correctly implements shared-secret authentication via the `X-Narrative-Auth` header, controlled by the `auth_token` setting. `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is used to secure the endpoints. No secrets are hardcoded or leaked in logs.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured, modular, and extensively tested. 85 tests related to the narrative API passed successfully. The `list_world_entities` implementation in `entities.py` includes a robust heuristic for pagination with local filtering to ensure clients receive the requested number of items even when using stores with varying filtering capabilities.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found. (A pre-existing `PermissionError` in `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py` was observed but determined to be unrelated to the current task scope).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The pagination heuristic in `list_world_entities` (`limit * 5` fetch) successfully balances store-side efficiency with local filtering correctness. The ASGI gap mentioned in previous notes is addressed for the primary entry points (`main()`), ensuring `bootstrap_identity()` is invoked during standard startup.\n"}}
