sdp/runner.log:27571:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-05-02T14:37:14.196Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task frac-0040\n\n**Task:** Deepen engine from depth 1 to depth 2: Simple: one-path implementation, functions produce meaningful output, end-to-end works\n**Tier:** T2\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nSimple: one-path implementation, functions produce meaningful output, end-to-end works\n\nHint: Implement the simplest working version of each function. One algorithm path, no edge cases. The system should work end-to-end with this module.\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n3. **Review specification** (if T2/T3):\n   Read `specs/frac-0040-spec.md`\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/frac-0040-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — frac-0040\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: **No tests for `GET /world/entities` — severity: blocking.** The acceptance criterion is not exercised. A `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` covering at minimum: (a) `domain=deniable` returns only deniable+shared; (b) no domain defaults to shared; (c) `type` filter; (d) pagination (`limit`, `offset`) must be added before this task is considered done..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: **Pagination may underdeliver under native-paginating stores — severity: minor.** If the backing store honours `limit`/`offset` natively but ignores `domain_filter`, post-filtering silently returns fewer than `limit` items per page. Consider fetching with a multiplier or delegating full pagination responsibility to the store..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: `domain=deniable` → only entities with `domain in {\"deniable\", \"shared\"}` returned..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: No `domain` param → only `domain=\"shared\"` entities returned..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: `type=character` filter narrows results..\n"}
